YEAH!  Thanks Rees!  I am still going to try an external antenna - or maybe
hang out my upper floor window with tinfoil attached to my appendages :-)

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Wiliam Clarke
Sent: Friday, March 28, 2008 11:54 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Re: New file uploaded to EVP-ITC



I can hear 95% of your files, and they are pretty clear!



Rees

Kristin Morris &lt;ckmorris95@...&gt; wrote:

Oh yeah.. one more thing..  You really don&#39;t hear anything more than the YES
IT DOES at the end?  This is killing me.. I can hear them so clearly and I&#39;m
boggled every time someone says they don&#39;t hear it as I do. Oh well.  I&#39;ll
keep trying for better audio.

K (more determined than ever! ;-)



  _____  


From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
itcdeadpeople
Sent: Friday, March 28, 2008 10:46 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: New file uploaded to EVP-ITC

Hi Kristin. I can hear the &quot;yes it does&quot; part. I looked up some of the
meanings of the word 
&#39;portal&#39; and found this:

&quot;A portal in fiction is a magical or technological doorway that connects two
distant 
locations.&quot;

I suppose in this regard the &#39;ghost boxes&#39; or radios used in sweep with the
intent of 
communication could be considered a portal of sorts, but if that is the
case, then wouldn&#39;t 
our digital recorders (which can be used by those in spirit to produce EVP
even when it is 
not our intent) and televisions, camcorders, ordinary cameras, etc (used by
those in spirit 
to show their images, again, with our without our intent) also be portals? I
recently got an 
EVP voicemail from my next door neighbor&#39;s mother, saying her name, and when
reversed, 
the message is &quot;I love you.&quot; So I guess we&#39;d have to toss telephones and
computers onto 
the list as well.

I think the truth is, those in spirit can (and do!) basically go wherever
they want, whenever 
they choose, and do not require our permission or our technology to do so.
The only thing 
the technology does is allow us to be aware of their presence, which in many
cases would 
have gone by unnoticed, if not for our use of the equipment. 

Just my thoughts on the subject. :0)

Margaret

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com,
&quot;Kristin&quot; &lt;ckmorris95@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Hey guys -I sent a message that apparently got lost in the
&gt; stratosphere but I sent this clip because I asked about the radio as a
&gt; portal thing back in early March and I got a fairly definite
&gt; affirmative answer on that. But who knows. I have have given
&gt; completely opposing views before but it is something to chew on.
&gt; k
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com,
EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Hello,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; This email message is a notification to let you know that
&gt; &gt; a file has been uploaded to the Files area of the EVP-ITC 
&gt; &gt; group.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; File : /Kristin&#39;s Files/Radio Portal.mp3 
&gt; &gt; Uploaded by : nitsirk65 &lt;ckmorris95@&gt; 
&gt; &gt; Description : I asked if the radio was used as a portal and I
&gt; received a pretty definate answer from them: EVERYTIME BACK&FORTH
&gt; TO&FROM BRING IT YES IT DOES 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; You can access this file at the URL:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; http://groups. &lt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/EVP-&gt; yahoo.com/group/EVP-
ITC/files/Kristin%27s%20Files/Radio%20Portal.mp3
